This paper discusses the use of smart contracts on the blockchain to address corruption in financial transactions. As such, it is likely to fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of blockchain technology. Additionally, the paper discusses the automation of financial transactions, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also touches on legal issues and disputes, which could fall under the category of computers and society (cs.CY).
